<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-09"><hi rend="italic">February 9,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Loomis instructs Mr. Conger to instruct the consul at Niu-chwang to
                            take charge of Japanese interests at the request of that Government in
                            the event of its consul being withdrawn, if China assents thereto. The
                            consul’s duties will be confined to the use of his good offices in
                            protecting Japanese subjects and their interests, but he will not be
                            invested with any Japanese consular fuctions or authority.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>